definition: to fish with a hook and bait
tool/device/utensil/equipment/instrument/talent/ability/to possess/to have/to provide/to furnish/to state/classifier for devices, coffins, dead bodies

sentences.english: I will get my rod and tackle box now .
sentences.chinese: 我现在就去拿我的钓杆和钓具箱。

sentences.english: The fishing tackle was held on the top of his car by ropes.
sentences.chinese: 他把钓具用绳子固定在他的汽车顶上。

sentences.english: The site currently markets and sells fishing tackle of all types to enthusiastic sport fishermen.
sentences.chinese: 站点目前向专业的钓鱼者推广和销售各种钓具。

sentences.english: These kinds of fish are caught with special tackle .
sentences.chinese: 这几种鱼是用专门的钓具钓的。

sentences.english: I'm thinking of starting up in the fishing tackle trade.
sentences.chinese: 我正考虑做钓具生意呢。

definition: variant of 漁具|渔具[yu2 ju4]
to fish with a hook and bait
variant of 魚鉤|鱼钩[yu2 gou1]
